[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man injured in serious assault in Gilmerton pub

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man is being treated for a chest injury after he was attacked in a pub in Gilmerton.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police Scotland said the serious assault happened inside a pub in Drum Street at around 14:40 on Sunday.
Officers said the 28-year-old man's injuries were not life-threatening.
They appealed for anyone with information about the attack to contact them.
